Datasets and Benchmarks
Widely used datasets include FER2013, CK+, RAF-DB, and AffectNet, which provide labeled images across standard emotion categories. Benchmark competitions such as the EmotioNet Challenge encourage algorithmic innovation, emphasizing performance under real-world variations in pose, lighting, and occlusion.

Challenges and Trends
FER faces persistent challenges including cross-cultural variability, spontaneous versus posed expressions, and fairness concerns across demographics. Current research trends emphasize domain adaptation, self-supervised learning, and explainability to improve generalization and ethical deployment in real-world environments.
